\section{Summary and Prospects}

In this report we discuss a method for calculating phase-space integrals for the off-diagonal time-like splitting functions based on the differential equations method.
This work is a part of the ongoing ab initio computation of the time-like splitting functions at next-to-next-to-leading order in QCD.
The key idea of our method is to find an appropriate basis for master integrals which leads to significant simplification of differential equations.
As a main result, we describe how to efficiently construct such a basis and find solutions of the resulting differential equations.
We also discuss how to fix boundary conditions from the Mellin moments.
To demonstrate how our method works in practice, we calculate master integrals for the decay processes $1 \to 4$ and $1 \to 3$ with an $x$-space projection, needed to extract NLO contributions to the off-diagonal time-like splitting function from $e^+e^-$ annihilation process.

